I sit in my room and I came across this... 

I lost my childhood to abusive people who literally tortured me for existing, had no friends or GFs for the 12 years I was in school, I was shunned because I was quiet, I was made fun of for everything, I watched every mothers day go by wanting my mommy who didn't even want me... when becoming an adult I watched people follow their goals and dreams while I had no one to be there to make working hard worthwhile, I was cheated on by 3 of 6 of my exes and the other 3 Exes just left me because I was the burden and loved too much, I lost friends and I'm the only family member who has nothing going for himself... 

It hurts a lot. And not the kind of hurt that simply goes away but the kind of hurt where I wanna curl up in the fetal position hugging a pillow to death and letting lose with my tears and just silently crying... 

Watching people succeed in life and being scared of doing anything because I'm afraid of becoming heartless and a shitty person... I wake up daily and pretend that people messaged me... 

The worse thing is how I go into my imagination world where I am a hero and people rely on me to save them and I even listen to epic music just to spice up my imagination battles and I imagine meeting someone who likes me and having many friends and I imagine that I save the world...

Cringey, I know... My imagination is what made my childhood spend being locked away and sitting in pure darkness, bearable. I would often imagine scenarios that I have people who loved me and cared for me and I imagined I had friends and silently talked to myself and I often would pretend I was a superhero with powers who saved many people.


And then I woke up and realized that I was the same worthless kid who deserved to be beaten, spit on, thrown in freezing cold showers while getting beaten half to death with a belt while shivering... But I deserved it, right? I mean, I would pass notes to this girl in class and it was a love letter but my aunt found the notes I would never get to pass to my crush and when I did, she and everyone else used to laugh at me... I even tried giving her my gold bracelet that I treasured because I thought it was the right thing to do for someone you liked... so many days and nights I spent crying and begging anyone to save me like superman or some other fictional character but then I realized no one was going to save me...


I look back and realized that I don't deserve to enjoy life... Its almost like a sign telling me that my fate is to suffer. I met this girl before I left overseas and we hit it off and she shared with me that she also liked me but the last day I was still at home, she told someone else that I was stupid for believing she liked me and she was joking around pretending to hold my hand, kiss me, and cuddle with me and she told everyone else that she hated every single moment with me... I went overseas on a deployment having my heart broken when I found out I was not gonna have anyone waiting on me when I got back home... worse is how when I got back home, I hit it off with this girl who really liked me and I even stayed with her where we shared so many happy memories and then one day she just decided to break up and told me that she wanted to be independent... How does one wake up one day on your own bed after dreaming that your special someone was still with you,  cuddling you in bed, and sleeping beside you, and realizing that you were all alone? Imagine sleeping with someone, watching anime with her, holding each other, celebrating birthdays together, sharing tender moments and sleeping together and they just decide one day that they didn't feel like being with you because they wanted to be independent and then you find out that your partner cheated on you, lied to you with their long trips to their "Parent's house", and they just grow distant with you despite you trying to shower them with real love and reminding them everyday that they are beautiful, amazing, their smile is to die for, and you work hard caring for their animals and cleaning their apartment so they could come home to a nice clean apartment and they just sit you down in their back porch while having the guy she will be with after she gives you a long winded speech about how it was your fault that she grew distant and that she felt like she was a parent to a child and she didn't like you being "overbearing" despite her doing the same thing and told me I was too insecure despite her going for her long 3 day trips to friend's homes to party and get drunk and have seggs with other dudes while you worked long hours and deal with abusive managers just to go back to her place and spending long nights alone in bed knowing that she will eventually leave me... 

She broke my heart. Nah, she did far morw than break my heart... She ripped my heart out of my chest, she whispered lies to it talking about "LoVe" and "A FuTuRe tOgEthEr" and stomped on it a few times and in the end handed it back to me expecting me to not cry and beg for her to try and work with me so i wouldn't lose her because she was the one true girl I truly loved deeply and she did things for me that made me feel like I was married to her and she spoiled me and gave me sweet loving when I was depressed and then suddenly, she just... Leaves. She doesn't even tell me everything in person. She ripped into me and really treated me like shit because she didn't even want me to hurt really bad... 

After the dust settled, she told me that she felt guilty for hurting me and lying to me. She said she wanted me to hate her so much that I just quit acknowledging her and that I was too nice and loving and she even told me after her depressing speech to me that I can't cry or be sad or feel negatively afterwards... She made me feel worthless and helpless. After I got back home I cried so hard I spent months crying every other night and feeling lonely and even scared... She didn't even tell me what really happened and why she shoved me away... So even til this day I'm scared of giving someone my time and my heart just to rip my heart to shreds... I've felt this way for 5 years now... I still dream about her sometimes... and I always wake up crying. What's worse is that I still love her like an idiot... But I did promise her that she was my last gf. I didn't want anyone else. 

Every day, I hurt. It just fucking hurts alot. To realize that you have quite alot of love to give someone but you don't have that someone to share your love with... I just don't wanna die alone... It hurts... It hurts alot... ğŸ˜”ğŸ¥ºğŸ˜¢ğŸ˜
